## 2026-07-09 — NCBI_API_KEY set; backend reliability partially improved, not closed; design/assets gap identified

- Human set `NCBI_API_KEY` (+ confirmed via Render dashboard that recent
  failed health-check events are now reporting healthy) in Render's
  production env vars, redeployed. Re-verified live via repeated `curl`
  against the real backend before and after:
  - Before the key: successful `POST /search` calls took 30-57s (when
    they succeeded at all); `/health` and the DB-only
    `GET /search/settings` stayed fast/reliable throughout, isolating the
    slowness to the outbound NCBI call specifically.
  - After the key + redeploy settled (redeploy itself caused ~1-2 min of
    502s on ALL endpoints including `/health`, expected instance-cycle
    noise, not a new bug): successful searches now complete in ~4.4s
    (was 30-57s) — the key clearly fixed the rate-limit-backoff
    component of the slowness.
  - Still open: ~1 in 3 search attempts still fails (502 or a full 30s
    timeout) even post-fix, while `/health`/`/search/settings` stay
    100% reliable in the same window. This isolates to something in the
    Render-egress-to-NCBI network path itself (connection-level
    timeouts, not 429s) — `backend/app/integrations/pubmed.py`'s retry
    loop (`_get`, lines 229-284) does retry on `httpx.HTTPError` (covers
    connect/read timeouts) up to `_MAX_RETRY_ATTEMPTS=3` at a 10s
    per-attempt timeout, so a fully-failing request can still burn up to
    ~40s before giving up. Not fixed yet — two options on the table for
    whoever picks this up: (a) just monitor, this may be transient
    external network flakiness between Render's free tier and NCBI that
    fluctuates on its own; (b) tune the retry budget (lower per-attempt
    timeout, e.g. 6s, and/or fewer attempts) so a genuinely-failing
    request fails fast into the existing `service_unavailable`
    graceful-degradation path (§13.6) instead of hanging ~30-40s. Not
    done without the human's go-ahead since it's a real behavior change,
    not just a config tweak.
- Separately investigated (on request): whether `design/assets/`'s
  Claude-Design `.dc.html` component prototypes (LLButton, LLPaperCard,
  LLSearchSettingsPanel, LLSavedListPanel, LLZoteroPushDialog,
  LLAbstractReader, LLToast, etc. — 20 files + support.js) are actually
