## 2026-07-11 — Live-latency incident: root-caused and fixed (PERF-1/2/3 merged)

- Incident: live search took 33-46s (user saw "nothing works"). Root
  cause measured, three-part: (1) Turso DB is in aws-ap-south-1 (Mumbai)
  vs Render in Oregon — ~250ms per DB statement; (2) N+1 patterns issued
  ~50-100 sequential statements per search; (3) new httpx client + TLS
  handshake per outbound NCBI/iCite call, 40s worst-case retry budget.
  Frontend compounded it: only a tiny inline spinner, Start re-clickable
  (stacking 40s requests), raw network errors rendered nothing.
- PERF-1 merged: search now 9 statements measured (was ~50-100);
  middleware down to ~1 statement steady-state; statement-count
  regression tests added. PERF-2 merged: pooled clients, 6s timeouts,
  ~13s worst-case failing call (was ~40s). PERF-3 merged: Start+Retry
  disabled while pending with "Searching…" label; network errors surface
  via ErrorState.
- Process: PERF-2/3 fully verified (tester + adversarial); PERF-1
  adversarial skipped on human token-conservation directive (see
  orchestrator.log). Ledger items: PubMed total-deadline wrapper;
  last_seen_at stale-branch test; SPEC §9.2 wording (60s-coarse
  last_seen_at); CONTRACTS.md note for client-only network_error code;
  cancel affordance for hung searches.
- OPEN, needs human: move Turso DB to aws-us-west-2 (create new DB, swap
  TURSO_DATABASE_URL/TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN in Render, redeploy) — remaining
  ~250ms×9 floor becomes ~5ms×9. Schema auto-creates; data is cache +
  ephemeral sessions, safe to abandon.
